Title: Basic Canon in D=4, N=1 Superfield Theory

Authors: S. James Gates, Jr

Comments: 1997 TASI Lectures, 109 pages, no figures, LaTeX twice

The topic of 4D, N = 1 supersymmetry is introduced for the reader with aprior background in relativistic quantum field theory. The presentation isdesigned to be a useful primer for those who plan to later engage in seriousinvestigation of the area or as an overview for the generally interested.